{
  "texts": [
    "2 Not only the number of references has increased, but over the years, the scope of GEAs has become more diverse.",
    "Today's environmental assessments draw on a much wider range of fields, including natural and social sciences, economics, anthropology, psychology, engineering and the humanities (Callaghan et al. 2020).",
    "Similarly, the readership of these reports has increased, from mostly negotiators and national governments in early assessments, to a range of (non)-governmental organisations, civil society, and businesses across the globe.",
    "Given the growth in environmental literature and the expanding scope and readership of global GEAs, traditional methods of synthesizing work are increasingly challenging.",
    "Assessing the evidence from many diverse sources and disciplines is an incredibly demanding task."
  ]
}